        <td class="comment-text"><div><span class="comment-copy">Well, lets see if I can explain. You start with a base image, and then make your changes, and commit those changes using docker, and it creates an image. This image contains only the differences from the base. When you want to run your image, you also need the base, and it layers your image on top of the base using a layered file system, in this case AUFS. AUFS merges the different layers together and you get  what you want, and you just need to run it. you can keep adding more and more images(layers) and it will keep only saving the diffs.</span> &ndash;&nbsp;<a href="/users/356788/ken-cochrane" title="5896 reputation" class="comment-user">Ken Cochrane</a> <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><span title="2013-04-19 20:30:34Z" class="relativetime-clean">Apr 19 at 20:30</span></span></div></td>
    </tr>
            
    <tr id="comment-23944052" class="comment" data-commentid="23944052">
        <td class="comment-actions"><table><tbody><tr>
<td class="comment-score">
<span title="number of 'useful comment' votes received" class="cool">1</span>
</td>
<td>
&nbsp;
</td></tr>
</tbody></table></td>
        <td class="comment-text"><div><span class="comment-copy">@Ken - Is docker.io a good bet given that aufs will not be supported in future ubuntu releases ? <a href="http://askubuntu.com/questions/279127/doesnt-raring-mainline-kernelppa-v-3-8-3-support-aufs" title="doesnt raring mainline kernelppa v 3 8 3 support aufs">askubuntu.com/questions/279127/&hellip;</a>. Also I want to get it working on ubuntu 13.04 (32 bit), any way I can do that ?</span> &ndash;&nbsp;<a href="/users/1345376/murtaza52" title="2473 reputation" class="comment-user">murtaza52</a> <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><span title="2013-05-20 10:38:41Z" class="relativetime-clean">May 20 at 10:38</span></span></div></td>
    </tr>
            
    <tr id="comment-23947141" class="comment" data-commentid="23947141">
        <td class="comment-actions"><table><tbody><tr>
